Version 1.0, July 2026

0. DEFINITIONS

"The Core" refers to the source code of the Juno compiler, its parsers, intermediate representation analyzers, code generators, and the Juno Standard Library ("stdlib").

"The Runtime" refers to the minimal compiled components of The Core (e.g., runtime object files, standard library bindings) that are technically necessary to execute programs compiled by The Core.

"The Output" refers to any executable binaries, object files, or assembly code generated by The Core from user-provided source code.

"Mega-Entity" refers to any legal entity, corporation, or group of affiliated entities whose gross annual revenue exceeds $10,000,000 (Ten Million US Dollars) or equivalent in local currency.

1. FREEDOM OF THE OUTPUT (RUNTIME EXCEPTION)

This License applies exclusively to The Core. The Output generated by The Core from your source code remains your sole property. The automatic inclusion or statutory linking of The Runtime into The Output does not subject The Output to the terms of this License. You have the absolute right to commercialize, distribute, and retain closed source code for your Output, subject only to the restrictions in Section 4.

2. VIRAL OPEN SOURCE REQUIREMENT (COPYLEFT)

If you modify The Core in any way and distribute these modifications (either as source code or as a compiled binary of the compiler), you must distribute the entirety of your modified version under the exact terms of this License. The creation of proprietary, closed-source derivatives or forks of The Core is strictly prohibited.

3. ANTI-EXPLOITATION SHIELD

No party may engage in the direct commercial exploitation of The Core itself. Prohibited exploitation includes, but is not limited to:
a) Providing access to The Core as a paid cloud service, Platform-as-a-Service (PaaS), or Compiler-as-a-Service.
b) Embedding The Core within proprietary Integrated Development Environments (IDEs) or software suites that require a fee for use.
c) Utilizing the source code of The Core to train proprietary or commercial Artificial Intelligence models.

4. THE MEGA-ENTITY RESTRICTION

If you meet the definition of a Mega-Entity (as defined in Section 0), the rights granted under Section 1 are explicitly revoked. Mega-Entities are strictly prohibited from using The Core to generate proprietary, closed-source Output for internal infrastructure, commercial products, or public distribution. 
To legally use The Core, a Mega-Entity must either:
a) Release the entirety of its generated Output under an OSI-approved Open Source license, or
b) Obtain a separate, explicitly negotiated commercial license directly from the original authors of The Core.

5. PATENT RETALIATION

By contributing code to The Core, you grant all users a perpetual, worldwide, royalty-free patent license to use your contributions. If you or your affiliated entity institute patent litigation against any party alleging that The Core infringes a patent, all rights previously granted to you under this License shall terminate immediately and permanently.

6. DISCLAIMER OF WARRANTY AND LIMITATION OF LIABILITY

THE CORE IS PROVIDED "AS IS", WITHOUT WARRANTY OF ANY KIND, EXPRESS OR IMPLIED. IN NO EVENT SHALL THE AUTHORS BE LIABLE FOR ANY CLAIM, DAMAGES, OR OTHER LIABILITY ARISING FROM, OUT OF, OR IN CONNECTION WITH THE SOFTWARE OR THE USE OR OTHER DEALINGS IN THE SOFTWARE.
